Whether Russia and China are cooperating or not, there is still the question why Russia's propaganda didn't trying to foment conflict with Iran or North Korea until Trump's presidency. After 2013 it became clear that Obama's foreign policy was timid, and Russia might have figured luring Obama into a war would be difficult. But fomenting public fear and distrust of Iran or North Korea under Obama wouldn't have hurt their efforts under the next president.

So it looks like they see Trump as especially suited for luring the U.S. into a costly war (or wars). Trump is even dumber than Bush, and his most trusted advisors are even more suspicious than Bush's advisors. If Bush could get suckered into Iraq, one would expect they could get Trump to do even worse. A proxy war with China would be particularly costly, since China could send in a lot more "volunteers" than Russia could:

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People's_Volunteer_Army

